2.  i'm glad to add this this weekend. i'll try to add target_shape and adj to deconv, then user can use its own pad, adj to desire the output shape, or just passed into data_shape, and the program will do it automatically.

I think there are several issues:

It is specialized for PC. If we use these, we can't make it run on ARM. So if we are going to support it under current code template, the device types will be like: `cpu, gpu, intel_cpu`, which seems a little bit strange, and redundant. Together with OpenCL issue, I think we may do a refactor on operator together with symbol.

